# Line-ending policy for this subtree, which is junction-shared with Homunculus-Weave
# (Expertises/TelegramSecretary -> here). Normalize text to LF so the same physical files
# stay consistent across both repos. Without this, plugins-weave's root (no .gitattributes
# + core.autocrlf=true) re-CRLFs .md on checkout, causing perpetual phantom-M in
# Homunculus-Weave whose policy is `* text=auto eol=lf`.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows batch files need CRLF — cmd.exe mis-parses LF-terminated lines.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf

# Shell scripts must stay LF: they run on Linux (cloud routine) where CRLF would break the
# shebang (#!/bin/bash). (Subsumed by the * rule above; kept explicit for intent.)
*.sh text eol=lf
